SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: Park West Cooperative Nursery School's Financial Aid ProgramAny current or prospective parents are eligible to apply for financial aid. On Park West's application is a box which parents can mark to receive information on applying for financial aid. In order to be eligible for financial aid, parents are required to fill out Park West forms, forms from our scholarship service, and also submit their most recent tax return. FACTS Business Solutions for Education is the scholarship service used by Park West. This service gathers the information from the families applying for financial aid and determines each family's ability to pay tuition and their expected family contribution. Park West's financial aid committee consists of the school director, the board of directors' president, treasurer, and membership committee chairs. The families are presented as Family A, Family B, etc. in order to maintain impartiality as well as parents' confidentiality. The estimated family contribution suggested by FACTS is used as a baseline. Financial aid awards are granted only for the current school year and are based on multiple factors. These include family need, the number of applicants requesting aid, and the amount allocated in Park West's operating budget for financial aid.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: ALL OFFICERS AND DIRECTORS ARE VOLUNTEERS EXCEPT FOR THE EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR AND TWO OTHER DIRECTORS. THE CHAIR OF THE PERSONNEL COMMITTEE WILL MAKE A RECOMMENDATION TO THE BOARD FOR COMPENSATION FOR ALL EMPLOYEES. THE BOARD WILL VOTE ON COMPENSATION RECOMMENDATIONS THE FOLLOWING MONTH. ALL COMPENSATION IS BASED ON PREVAILING WAGE RATES IN CHICAGO FOR SIMILAR POSITIONS.
